# Node.js / Backend Standards

## API Design

- REST only; versioned at `/api/v1/`
- Consistent response envelope:
  ```json
  { "data": ..., "error": null, "meta": {} }
  { "data": null, "error": { "code": "...", "message": "..." } }
  ```
- Use correct HTTP status codes: 200 / 201 / 400 / 401 / 403 / 404 / 422 / 500

## MongoDB / Mongoose

- Define explicit Mongoose schemas with full validation — no bare objects
- Derive TypeScript types from schemas using `InferSchemaType` — no duplicate interfaces
- Use aggregation pipelines for financial calculations (sums, averages, grouping)
- Index all fields used in query filters and sort operations

## Error Handling

- All async route handlers must catch errors — no unhandled promise rejections
- Structured error logging: include request method, path, user context when available
- Never expose stack traces or internal errors to the client in production
- Centralized error handler middleware at the end of the Express/Fastify chain

## Security

- All secrets and config via `.env` — never hardcoded
- Validate and sanitize all incoming request data before use
- `.env` file is always in `.gitignore`
- Use `helmet` (Express) or equivalent for HTTP security headers
